description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cardiac Theatres - Band 5 Staff Nurse (Theatres) Experienced - Theatres, Anaesthesia and Perioperative Medicine (TAP)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in two of London’s most sort after locations, Guy&#39;s and St Thomas’ TAP (Theatres Anaesthesia and Perioperative Medicine) Directorate is looking for experienced Band 5 Scrub Nurses to join our highly skilled team in the Cardiac theatres, cardiac scrub experience is not required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an experienced scrub nurse, are you looking to further develop your career and expand your skills within the Cardiovascular setting - this may be the area for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This theatre suite located on the St Thomas’ site is comprised of 4 cardiac operating theatres and a Hybrid Endovascular suite. As a tertiary referral centre we offer a wealth of experience. Our long history of cutting edge surgery means that you could be involved in some of the worlds most advanced procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can we offer you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want you to be the best you can be and promise to support you in achieving your goals through our in-house training programs and tertiary study at our affiliated universities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training and support is provided whilst we develop your existing skills and knowledge in each aspect of the Perioperative environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personal and professional growth is encouraged through work based learning programs. These programs cover a broad range of clinical and non-clinical skills that aid you in building your professional portfolio in advanced nursing, leadership, research and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Academy aims to develop a team of practitioners, with knowledge and skills to care for patients within Theaters, Anesthesia and Perioperative Medicine (TAP), recognizing the commitments of our staff and rewarding achievements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further information on the directorate and TAP academy can be found in the Fact sheet and booklet attached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please be advised that all the interviews will be conducted online via Skype, and there will be no phone interviews. Please make sure that you have a Skype account and the video and audio functions are working.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews to be conducted online via Skype for Business or Microsoft Teams on the week commencing the 14th of December 2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
